  <title>SET DECIMALS Command</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Commands</keyword>
    <keyword>Decimals<keyword>setting number of places</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Displaying<keyword>numbers</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Environment</keyword>
    <keyword>SET DECIMALS command</keyword>
    <keyword>Setting<keyword>decimal places</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SET DECIMALS Command</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="__CommandInclude" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Purpose</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Change the setting that determines the number of decimal places used to display numbers.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Syntax</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET DECIMALS TO [&lt;<text styleclass="Italic">nDecimals</text>&gt;]</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Heading1">Description</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">SET DECIMALS TO with no argument is equivalent to SET DECIMALS TO 0. &#160;SET DECIMALS is functionally equivalent to SetDecimal(). &#160;</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><snippet src="__IncludeLibRT" inline="false"/></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
